      <h2 class="about-bio-text-header">My story:</h2>
      <p class="about-bio-text">I was diagnosed over 20 years ago, when no one seemed to know how to help me. I doubled my weight at 5-years-old and was diagnosed with PCOS at 12. After countless judgmental doctors, dietitians, endocrinologist, etc… my parents and I still had very few answers, except:</p>
      <ul class="about-ulist">
        <li>1) “You must be lying about your diet.”</li>
        <li>2) “You will never be thin skinny.”</li>
        <li>3) “You will never be able to have kids.”</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="about-bio-text">Ouch.</p>
      <p class="about-bio-text">The only advice I was given: “Just lose weight.” (You too? Let’s talk.) </p>
    </div>
