      <h2 class="about-bio-text-header">My journey:</h2>
      <p class="about-bio-text">No matter what I tried, the weight always came back. I felt like my own body was fighting me and I had no control. I also developed an eating disorder, obsessed over the number on the scale, and hated myself.</p>
      <p class="about-bio-text">After I graduated with a degree in education, I decided to get weight loss surgery. But, guess what? THE WEIGHT STILL CAME BACK!</p>
      <h2 class="about-bio-text-header">Then, I realized something:</h2>
      <p class="about-bio-text">I realized this was more than just about needing to “just lose weight.”</p>
      <ul class="about-ulist">
        <li>It’s NOT about the scale.</li>
        <li>It’s NOT about carbs.</li>
        <li>I am NOT broken.</li>
        <li>I just need HELP.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="about-bio-text">So, I went back to school and became a registered dietitian. After over 1,200 hours of supervised practice and starting a local support group for people with PCOS, I found my calling. Helping others helped me too. I realized I wasn’t alone and it helped to talk with people who understood my journey.</p>
      <ul class="about-ulist">
        <li>I FINALLY understood my body.</li>
        <li>I FINALLY felt in control of my body.</li>
        <li>I FINALLY found tools that helped me lose weight and stick with it!</li>
        <h2 class="about-bio-text-header">AND I’M HERE TO HELP YOU TOO!</h2>
      </ul>
